fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hζ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/RootsOfUnity/PrimitiveRoots.html#IsPrimitiveRoot\">IsPrimitiveRoot</a> <span class=\"fn\">ζ</span> (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">u</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Units/Defs.html#Units\">ˣ</a>) (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Discriminant.html#Algebra.discr\">Algebra.discr</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Rat/Basic.html#Rat\">ℚ</a> <span class=\"fn\">⇑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/Cyclotomic/PrimitiveRoots.html#IsPrimitiveRoot.subOnePowerBasis\">IsPrimitiveRoot.subOnePowerBasis</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Rat/Basic.html#Rat\">ℚ</a> <span class=\"fn\">hζ</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerBasis.html#PowerBasis.basis\">basis</a></span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">u</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">p</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `p` is a prime and `IsCyclotomicExtension {p ^ k} K L`, then there are `u : ℤˣ` and\n`n : ℕ` such that the discriminant of the power basis given by `ζ - 1` is `u * p ^ n`. Often this is\nenough and less cumbersome to use than `IsCyclotomicExtension.Rat.discr_prime_pow'`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/Cyclotomic/Basic.html#IsCyclotomicExtension.Rat.discr_prime_pow_eq_unit_mul_pow'","kind":"theorem","line":68,"name":"IsCyclotomicExtension.Rat.discr_prime_pow_eq_unit_mul_pow'","sourceLink":"https